abstract: Hopeful but also afraid. Uncertain but still focused. Iowa's Democrats will arrive at their 2020 kickoff caucuses on Monday with a mix of emotions and one urgent mission: voting President Donald Trump out of office in November.

headline_main: Iowa in Focus: Democrats Open 2020 With Hope, Anxiety
headline_print_headline: Iowa in Focus: Democrats Open 2020 With Hope, Anxiety

abstract: It’s really, finally, happening. This is your morning tip sheet.
snippet: It’s really, finally, happening. This is your morning tip sheet.
lead_paragraph: CEDAR RAPIDS, Iowa — On the morning after Hillary Clinton lost in November 2016, I stood wedged between television cameras, in the back of a hotel ballroom, and watched a Democratic breakdown.

abstract: Democratic party officials in Iowa worked furiously Tuesday to deliver the delayed results of their first-in-the-nation caucus, as frustrated presidential candidates claimed momentum and plowed ahead in their quest for the White House.
snippet: Democratic party officials in Iowa worked furiously Tuesday to deliver the delayed results of their first-in-the-nation caucus, as frustrated presidential candidates claimed momentum and plowed ahead in their quest for the White House.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — Democratic party officials in Iowa worked furiously Tuesday to deliver the delayed results of their first-in-the-nation caucus, as frustrated presidential candidates claimed momentum and plowed ahead in their quest for the White House.

abstract: On the brink of actual voting, the party that preached of unity to defeat President Trump finds itself very divided.

abstract: Patrick Mahomes led the Chiefs to three fourth-quarter touchdowns as Kansas City won its first Super Bowl title in 50 years.
snippet: Patrick Mahomes led the Chiefs to three fourth-quarter touchdowns as Kansas City won its first Super Bowl title in 50 years.
lead_paragraph: MIAMI GARDENS, Fla. — After a 50-year wait, the Kansas City Chiefs are Super Bowl champions once again, after Patrick Mahomes engineered a stirring fourth-quarter comeback Sunday to beat the San Francisco 49ers, 31-20, at a raucous Hard Rock Stadium.
